  "Descendant of the storied Bangur clan of Kolkata, Krishna Kumar Bangur chairs graphite electrodes-maker Graphite India.",
  "The $507 million (revenue) company was set up in 1962 in collaboration with Great Lakes Carbon, an American firm.",
  "The company, which supplies leading steelmakers in India and overseas, is the world's third-largest producer of graphite electrodes. ",
  "It has lately benefitted from China's decision to replace polluting blast furnaces with electric arc furnaces to make steel. "
